</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unucle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nucle</A> at: 4/29/01 1:34:08 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uskystormthunderbolt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SkystormThunderbolt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/01 2:32:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would someone mind helping me out wtih some info?</span><hr size=1> level 38 is a good level to go to Overthere, You've not kited much? Here is my suggestions:<br>
<br>
* Get a staff of the temperate flux if you haven't one already.<br>
* Get JBoots or a heap of sow potions, or bring some donating money with you.<br>
* Find a friendly Enchanter in zone that you can donate to for clarity.<br>
<br>
Now you are ready to kite.<br>
<br>
Go to Fronteir Mountains ledge and turn left, make camp in the corner (it is reletavely safe, just med up the wall a bit).<br>
When your ready go out and snare yourself a plant, bird or Sarnak. (The others have sow and many hps)<br>
Once you have it snared run towards your camp spamming your staff of temp flux, as soon as you see the &quot;Target is out of range&quot; stop and start spamming your biggest DD until it casts. Rinse and repeat until the mob is dead, loot, med then re-do.<br>
<br>
Sometimes it doesn't go as smooth as that, if snare doesn't stick then run in a straight line until the mob is 'Out of range' while checking it with your staff. Stop when the mob is out of range and spam root. If root doesn't stick run in a straight line (towards a zoneline), try to root again, if that doesn't stick I would contemplate zoning - a resistable mob like that will resist most of your spells and isn't worth the risk.<br>
<br>
If root does stick one of those times - snare it when it is rooted and DD as normal.<br>
<br>
Soloing isn't the most exciting way of getting exp - but it is a very plausable way of exping. The thing you have to keep in mind is your surroundings, be as careful as possible, don't take un-necessary risks - they will get you killed.<br>
<br>
Good luck<br>
<br>
Skystorm Thunderbolt<br>
45th Wizard - Tholuxe Paells <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaeanorendarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeanor Endarion</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/picon.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/01 8:17:09 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would someone mind helping me out wtih some info?</span><hr size=1> You don't have to snare kite to solo in that level range. I sat in the porch to the tunnel to Burning Woods on the Frontier Mountains side and root-nuked everything blue that walked by. Be cared with some of the giants; braes and tumps should be fine, craigs you shouldn't attempt till after 40. Cenobites are evil bad news, they are clerics, heal a lot, and interupt you with Wrath. Everything else is fairly easy. Keep Steelskin up for when root breaks, re-root and refresh it, then keep on nuking. The zone is close if you have trouble. Now that BoF and root stack, you can BoF them too and take much less damage than I had to put up with, but it is busy around there, and kiting may make it tough to keep a single pull single. <p><b>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvaliso.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valiso</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://homepages.go.com/~valiso/flash.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/1/01 9:23:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would someone mind helping me out wtih some info?</span><hr size=1> If you want to try to ae kite something to make sure you can do it with the mob you want to ae, snarr that mob and use your ae spell that your going to use if you can kill it with that spell try adding another mob next time or when you feel your ready.<br>
 When  i ae mobs i pull with staff of flux and have it run and me unsnarred till i find another mob to add to the pull, when both mobs are runing behind you find a nice clear area and run in a big but tight circal till both mobs are as one, when the mobs are togeather run away from there and cast your ae snarr &quot; only cast it if you feel you have enough room to get the spell off&quot; Now the trick is to pray to god both snarr<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  if one is unsnard you can just root it camp and try again or snarr the mob that missed it the first time and reround up both mobs till there togeather again and resnarr them both (note by resnarring them your mana may be to low to kill them so be carful) If both mobs snarr the second time start your ae'ing. If you feel you will not have enough mana to kill both try nuking one of the mobs till it dies then just root the other and play the med root game till you have enough mana to kill it. <p><center>
